result.name: Yamaton

reviews.text: Terrible food. This quality of the food at this Japanese/Korean fusion restaurant is very poor. The meat in the beef dinner set was as so tough that half of it was indigestible.  The only redeeming quality is that we managed to get a table for six people without booking at 7pm on  a Friday night. We know now that there is a reason for that. The service was fine and unobtrusive. As a place to hang out in a group in the middle of MK, this place is adequate, but if quality of food is important to you, I would not go here. There are several more options just one floor up.
You must try the gyoza!

Surprisingly good and I like the hotpot that come in mountain of vege and meat which have to let it cook for awhile before eat.. The portion is quite big for 2 person but overall the staff and manager is very polite.. Good service attitude! Will definitely be back again.. 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
Good selection, interesting juices, no tea though!!!
Excellent service n ambiance for a nice pork cutlet and lunch

reviews.text: Food's nothing special, and the preparation was completely abysmal. One of the orders took forever to arrive. The noodles got here first, but the sides, even though it should be easy to prepare,  came when the noodles were almost finished. And to top it off, the sides were cold and somewhat raw. The experience here left a bad taste in our mouths, and we will never come here again.
out of our expectation, good. also good in service & spacious seatings.
